post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has led to medical discrimination.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If government regulations lead to drugs being expensive, it is possible people will still try to access cheaper drugs on a black market and these drugs may still be dangerous or of poor quality. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help drive down the profits of drug cartels since people could get their drugs from legal reliable sources. Hence it may force the cartels to offer a purer product or less expensive to remain competitive. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Cheap drugs means more drugs for the same money, which could lead to more addiction problems.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only true in the case of people whose drug use either causes them to become dangerous or interferes with their lives. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalization of recreational drug use is not necessary for legalization of expanded drug research. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research chemicals, which are used as [date rape drugs](https://drugabuse.com/date-rape-drugs/), are constantly evolving and changing formulations to escape existing regulation. It is unlikely that the law would be able to control all of them. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addictive drugs increasingly reduce one's ability to do without them, and therefore they can inhibit freedom. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates negatively with socially-responsible behavior. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In many legal frameworks, the use of drugs is not considered a criminal offense. Only production, commerce, ownership and distribution of drugs are typically illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A more substantial part of society will be exposed to the harmful and dangerous side effects of drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of all drugs will promote newer, and safer drugs being developed to combat the negative side effects of dangerous drugs such as methamphetamines or heroin. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If an individual is already addicted, that would indicate they already have regular access to the drug.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A society where everyone consumes moderate amounts of drugs wouldn't be much different than the societies of today. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The culture of [overprescription](https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2018/06/opioid-epidemic/563576/) in the medical community has been a significant factor in the opioid crisis. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration of drug users impacts their families.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs should not be a prerequisite for better education. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Entheogenic drugs](https://maps.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5468), such as psychedelics, have been used throughout human history for many benefits in evolutionary growth and cognitive development.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Holland, [a channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvRQKXtIGcK1yEnQ4Te8hWQ) exists just to raise awareness of drugs. It explains how and when to take them, and what to do when a friend is having an OD.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing would lead to a better understanding of addiction in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Safety of irresponsible people shouldn't come at the expense of freedom of responsible people."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This claim is speculative. The correlation between drugs and \\(violent\\) crime is observable. The causes for that correlation are not necessarily observable.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Incarceration](https://beckleyfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/paper_07.pdf) of drug offenders is expensive and a burden on taxpayers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "[Ricin](https://emergency.cdc.gov/agent/ricin/facts.asp), a highly poisonous substance, is created from castor beans. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The right to bodily integrity protects individuals from [forced labor, slavery or torture](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodily_integrity).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The risk of unknown purity and poor-quality drugs will be minimized. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Dangerous substitute drugs will be contained. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Recreational drugs can be used as self medication especially for those with severe mental health issues like PTSD and psychosis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If only leaving syringes was punishable, and not use or possession of drugs, they would put in the extra effort to _not_ break the law at all. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalising drugs related to date rape could bring the issue further into the public eye, allowing for more widespread education on the topic.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are an experience that can build character.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tracing the rapist after the rape does not undo the rape itself, as the harm was already done.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs would not be the only option; there may still be a market of illegal drugs, for example if it is cheaper than the legal choice.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2014, [8.7%](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-healthcare-costs-smoking-idUSKBN0JX2BE20141219) of all healthcare spending in the US was spent on tobacco-related illnesses.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation does not necessarily mean that drugs will be freely available. It is easier to control and regulate drugs when they are legalised as governments can restrict who can make and sell them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If state distributed drugs freely as a prescription medicine for registered addicts, it could seriously harm the income from organized crime.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legalised, people who are addicted may feel more comfortable seeking help and support as they won't be viewed as criminals in the way they currently are. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The drug industry, like alcohol and tobacco, can be heavily taxed, generating high revenues. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If established companies behave inappropriately with regards to the selling of drugs, people would be able to report this without fear of facing consequences for trying to buy drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
